HEADWORD: Karyomiton
<hw>Kar`y*om"i*ton</hw>
<pr>(k⟦acr⟧r`⟦icr⟧*⟦ocr⟧m"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
Gr. <grk>ka`ryon</grk> a nut + <grk>mi`tos</grk> a thread.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The reticular network of fine fibers, of which
the <xex>nucleus</xex> of a cell is in part composed; -- in opposition
to <contr>kytomiton</contr>, or the network in the <xex>body</xex> of
the cell.</def> <rj><au>W. Flemming.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>karyoplasma</ent>⟦br⟧
